Clustering Algorithms => unsupervised learning machine learning task. 
Automatically discovering natural groupings in data. 

Two main Algorithms 
K means Clustering & Hierachical Clustering 


K means clustering => tools for discovering categories in groups in the any dataset. 
Take a simple scatter plot using just two variables, x and y, k means makes it easy to 
identify clusters in a specific dataset. 
Kmeans works with multidimensional dataset and it is designed to find clusters in the dataset 
to aid in decision making. 


Hierachical Clustering => group similar objects or data pts into groups called cluster. 

Step 1  
Make each data point a single-point cluster -> That forms N Clusters

Step 2 
Take the two closest data pt and make them one cluster -> and that forms N-1 clusters 

Step 3 
Take the two closest clusters and make them one cluster -> and that forms N-2 clusters 

Step 4 
Repeat STEP 3 until there is one cluster. 